sub_title: Event Manager @ Superconnectors || International Business Student
summary:
Since I was a child, one of my strongest personal traits has been my curiosity. I've always been eager to learn and understand more. This has helped me thrive in all of the positions I’ve taken as a student and an employee, as I am willing to acquire new knowledge and skills.

My great desire to get to know different cultures and countries encouraged me to pursue a Bachelor's degree in International Business, while working part-time and still actively participating as a SIP-Bulgaria board member and group leader. 

With all this happening, I always seem to be organizing something, whether it is an upcoming event, a group project, or just my weekly schedule. Writing long to-do lists and multi-step plans is a part of my routine, so if you need someone to solve a mess or coordinate your project, I might be a great fit.

My coworkers and friends describe me as positive and full of energy. When I am not working, I'll probably be hiking, reading, or discussing creative ideas that get me overexcited.
